How to set up GitHub Secrets (step-by-step)

This is the next real action, and it’s simple.

Step 1: Go to your GitHub repo
Repo → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions

Step 2: Add the required secret

Click “New repository secret”

Secret 1 (REQUIRED)
Field	Value
Name	GITHUB_OIDC_ROLE_ARN
Value	arn:aws:iam::<ACCOUNT_ID>:role/<ROLE_NAME>

Example:

arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/github-actions-oidc-role


This role will be created later via Terraform.

Optional (future — do NOT add now unless ready)
Secret	When
SONAR_TOKEN	When SonarQube exists
SONAR_HOST_URL	Same
Step 3: Verify secret availability

You don’t need to print it.

This line in the workflow will fail loudly if it’s missing:

role-to-assume: ${{ env.IAM_ROLE_ARN }}


That’s enough validation.